Talent International is searching for a ** Senior Application Specialist
(ServiceNow) ** to join our ** State Government ** client based in ** Brisbane
CBD ** on an initial contract until EOFY 2024 ** ** \+ extension options.

  
** // Senior Application Specialist (ServiceNow) **

** // Competitive daily rate on offer **

** // Brisbane CBD location (hybrid working available) **   

** The role: **   
The Senior Application Specialist (ServiceNow) will Provide high level
technical expertise and knowledge in application development, reporting and
database technologies to develop and support integrated business solutions.

** In this role you will: **

  * Undertake minor developments, and user administration activities of the agency's Service Now instance in accordance with the agency's Software Development principles and standards of the Queensland Government Enterprise Architecture . 
  * Monitor the agencies ServiceNow instance to ensure availability and timely escalation of any support issues. 
  * Administer and configure the agencies Service Now Instance, ensuring configuration changes are documented, tested and released in accordance with the agencies policies and procedures. 
  * Must have experience in workflow designing in different platforms such as ServiceNow, Resolve Software Group. Must have experience in web services such as REST and SOAP methodology. 
  * Must be experienced in HTML, Java, .net coding languages as these skills are needed in configuration new changes in the Resolve Software Application. 
  * Basic understanding of Resolve Software Group application is desired. 
  * Basic understanding of Case management is desired 

** Essential Requirements: **

  * Demonstrated knowledge and experience in designing, coding and testing web applications. Demonstrated knowledge and experience in reporting and analytics. 
  * Demonstrated Knowledge of IT Service Management (Including Helpdesk, ITIL Incident, Problem and Change Management). 
  * Highly developed interpersonal, written and oral communication skills with business and technical staff on the process of application development as part of service management. 
  * Proven ability to rapidly absorb new information and apply it effectively. 
  * Proven ability to select appropriately from applicable standards, methods, tools and applications. 

  
** Qualifications, professional registration, conditions and other requirements: **

  * A degree level qualification in information technology or computer science is highly regarded in this field. Development, administration and configuration experience using the Service Now platform will be highly regarded. 
  * Qualifications of ITIL v4 certificate and/or Application Developer - ServiceNow will be desirable for this position. 

  
